/setvar portuguese_compare {filebank4}


/model ${model_judge}
/multiline
Create a comprehensive summary report comparing ${model_translator} translations against canonical versions for Article ${article_num} across all 9 languages.

For each language (french, spanish, german, chinese, russian, arabic, italian, portuguese, japanese), provide:
1. Overall fidelity score (average of all criteria)
2. Most significant deviations found
3. General assessment of ${model_translator}  translation quality for that language
4. Common patterns of error across languages

Then provide:
- Overall quality rating for ${model_translator} as a translation model
- Strengths and weaknesses observed
- Languages where it performed best and worst
- Recommendations for improving translation quality

Here are the comparisons done earlier
${japanese_compare}
${french_compare}
${spanish_compare}
${german_compare}
${chinese_compare}
${russian_compare}
${arabic_compare}
${italian_compare}
${portuguese_compare}
;;
/multiline
/save ${trans_dir}/article${article_file_num}_summary_${model_translator}_comparison.txt

echo "All translations and comparisons complete! Results saved in ${trans_dir}/"
